me Pine (song)|Trail of the Lonesome Pine]]'' (1925)\n*''Toot Toot Tootsie'' (1926)\n*''Tramp, Tramp, Tramp, the Boys Are Marching'' (May 1926) (silent; sound re-issue)<ref>[http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/T/TrampTrampTrampTheBoys1926.html SilentEra entry says originally released silent, may have been reissued 1928 by Weiss Brothers-Artclass Pictures]</ref>\n*''Waiting for the Robert E. Lee'' (1926)\n*''When I Leave This World Behind'' (1926)\n*''When I Lost You'' (1926) (sound)<ref>[http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/W/WhenILostYou1926.html SilentEra entry]</ref>\n*''When the Midnight Choo-Choo Leaves for Alabam''' (1926) (sound)<ref>[http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/W/WhenTheMidnightChooCho1926.html SilentEra entry]</ref>\n*''Yak-A-Doola-Hick-A-Doola'' (1926) (sound)<ref>[http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/Y/YakaHulaHickaOoola1926.html SilentEra entry]</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[History of animation]]\n*[[Sound film]]\n*[[Phonofilm]]\n*[[RCA Photophone]]\n\n==Sources==\n*[[Leonard Maltin]], ''Of Mice and Magic: A History of the American Animated Film'' (1980, revised 1987)\n*[[Richard Fleischer]], ''Out of the Inkwell: Max Fleischer and the Animation Revolution'' (2005)\n*[[Ray Pointer]], ''Max Fleischer's Ko-Ko Song Car-tunes (with the Famous Bouncing Ball)'' DVD (2002)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/indexes/earlySoundFilms.html List of Early Sound Films 1894-1929 at Silent Era website]\n\n{{Fleischer Studios}}\n\n[[Category:Film series introduced in 1924]]\n[[Category:Film series disestablished in 1927]]\n[[Category:Animated film series]]\n[[Category:1920s American animated films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Fleischer Studios series and characters]]\n[[Category:Sing-along]]\n", "name_user": "Red dwarf", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHistory", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Song_Car-Tunes"}
{"title_page": "Sosnovaya Roshcha", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Sosnovaya Roshcha\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0421\u043e\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0420\u043e\u0449\u0430\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Sokolsky District, Vologda Oblast|Sokolsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|59|28|N|40|19|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/sokolskiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0421\u043e\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Sosnovaya Roshcha''' ({{lang-ru|\u0421\u043e\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0420\u043e\u0449\u0430}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Kadnikov, [[Sokolsky District, Vologda Oblast|Sokolsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 377 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Sokol, Vologda Oblast|Sokol]] is 13&nbsp;km, to Kadnikov is 1&nbsp;km. Kadnikov is the nearest rural locality.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Sokolsky District, Vologda Oblast}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Sokolsky District, Vologda Oblast]]\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Sosnovaya Roshcha\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0421\u043e\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0420\u043e\u0449\u0430\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Sokolsky District, Vologda Oblast|Sokolsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code           