{"title_page": "Morana (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|1994 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Morana\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Ale\u0161 Verbi\u010d]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = [[Samo Kuscer]]\n| starring       = [[Tanja Dimitrievska]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|1994}}\n| runtime        = 104 minutes\n| country        = Slovenia\n| language       = Slovene\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Morana''''' is a 1994 Slovenian [[horror film]] directed by [[Ale\u0161 Verbi\u010d]].<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/movies/movie/434811/Morana/overview |title=Morana |accessdate=1 October 2015 |work=NY Times}}</ref> The film was selected as the Slovenian entry for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[67th Academy Awards]], but was not accepted as a nominee.<ref>Margaret Herrick Library, Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Tanja Dimitrievska]] as Mojca\n* [[Damjana Grasic]] as Milena\n* [[Urska Hlebec]] as Vesna\n* [[Iztok Jereb]] as Vladimir\n* [[Zoran More]] as Samo\n* [[Pavle Ravnohrib]] as Borut\n* [[Natasa Tic Ralijan]] as Ana (as Natasa Ralijan)\n* [[Borut Veselko]] as Crt\n* [[Branko Zavrsan]] as Gorazd\n* [[Vojko Zidar]] as Rado\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 67th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[List of Slovenian submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n*[[Morana (goddess)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0110564|Morana}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Morana}}\n[[Category:1994 films]]\n[[Category:1994 horror films]]\n[[Category:Slovenian films]]\n[[Category:Slovene-language films]]\n[[Category:Folk horror films]]\n\n{{Slovenia-film-stub}}\n{{1990s-horror-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1994 film}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Morana\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Ale\u0161 Verbi\u010d]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = [[Samo Kuscer]]\n| starring       = [[Tanja Dimitrievska]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|1994}}\n| runtime        = 104 minutes\n| country        = Slovenia\n| language       = Slovene\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Morana''''' is a 1994 Slovenian [[horror film]] directed by [[Ale\u0161 Verbi\u010d]].<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/movies/movie/434811/Morana/overview |title=Morana |accessdate=1 October 2015 |work=NY Times}}</ref> The film was selected as the Slovenian entry for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[67th Academy Awards]], but was not accepted as a nominee.<ref>Margaret Herrick Library, Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Tanja Dimitrievska]] as Mojca\n* [[Damjana Grasic]] as Milena\n* [[Urska Hlebec]] as Vesna\n* [[Iztok Jereb]] as Vladimir\n* [[Zoran More]] as Samo\n* [[Pavle Ravnohrib]] as Borut\n* [[Natasa Tic Ralijan]] as Ana (as Natasa Ralijan)\n* [[Borut Veselko]] as Crt\n* [[Branko Zavrsan]] as Gorazd\n* [[Vojko Zidar]] as Rado\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 67th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[List of Slovenian submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n*[[Morana (goddess)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0110564|Morana}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Morana}}\n[[Category:1994 films]]\n[[Category:1994 horror films]]\n[[Category:Slovenian films]]\n[[Category:Slovene-language films]]\n[[Category:Folk horror films]]\n\n{{Slovenia-film-stub}}\n{{1990s-horror-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morana_(film)"}
